I love risotto, (almost always order it whenever I dine out) and have made this recipe several times. I like to use an assortment of mushrooms (at least 3), and have found that literally any combination renders fabulous results. The trick to a really creamy risotto is 1) use a wooden spoon! and 2) gently and slowly fold in the liquid, similar technique to making a souffle. For me, it takes much longer than 20 minutes for the liquid to absorb, but being patient pays off, this is better than anything I've had in any restaurant!

