I tried this recipe out for a group of girlfriends last night and it was a perfect combo of flavors! I made it as-is except: reduced the amount of onion to 1 total for the recipe (1/2 with the shrooms, 1/2 with the rice) and finished with a bit of truffle oil instead of chopped truffles. As always, I needed a couple of more cups of stock than called for. A couple of notes on past reviews: *Truffles have a unique flavor. If you are unfamiliar with it you might want to try it first before embarking on a relatively expensive dinner recipe for the first time. *I had no probelm with the leeks changing the texture- I did, however, cook them until the moisture had mostly evaporated *The mushrooms really did take about 45 min for me. I roasted them until all moisture was gone and they started to carmelize. I stirred them every 10-15 min throughout and kept expecting them to be done- per other reviews. Just goes to show, YMMV. When I make this again I will make the following changes: *Will probably skip the leeks all together- not sure they added much to this dish but the cream sure adds calories! *Reduce the amount of butter all around. I will use 1 TB for the shrooms, 1 tb for the onions & rice and 1 TB to finish. It simply doesn't need more than that! *Increase the number of shrooms, or possibly reserve them and serve on top instead of mixed in. I don't love shrooms but these were delish and I felt they got lost in the dish!

