Rating: 4
This is delicious, but with this recipe "Less REALLY is MORE"! It's intended as a first course but I I decided to half the recipe and serve it as an entree' for two (BIG mistake). I cut everything in 1/2, except that I used one cup of rice and adjusted the broth accordingly. I also omitted the truffles, so the proportion of rich ingredients to rice and broth was less than this recipe calls for. Despite my attempts to lighten it up, it was OVERWHELMINGLY rich-- too much to serve as an entree'-- and my proportions were huge for 2 people because of the intensity of flavors. I will make this again but will reduce the amount of whipping cream, butter and even mushrooms considerably. Despite decreasing the proportion of mushrooms, the intense shiitake flavor was just too much for us. It's a very special dish, but only appropriate as a first course (as the recipe was intended) or as a small entree'.

