Rating: 4
This is the best risotto I have ever made, and that's without the truffles or truffle oil (out of my budget). Like others, I found that the mushrooms and onions took only about 25 minutes to roast. I also found that my 2 leeks yielded about 4 cups when chopped, rather than 2. I used them all and did not find it to be too "leeky". This recipe is less time-consuming than it looks because you can get the main risotto part going while you roast the mushrooms and cook the leeks.

Rating: 4
